UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Offie Gene EVANS, Defendant-Appellant. No. 72-2689

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 21, 1972. Richard R. Kirby, Atlanta, Ga. (Court-appointed), for defendant-appellant. John W. Stokes, U. S. Atty., George H. Connell, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., Atlanta, Ga., for plaintiff-appellee.

Before THORNBERRY, COLEMAN and INGRAHAM, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5 Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409.

 PER CURIAM:

This is an appeal from an order denying appellant’s motion to dismiss the indictment against him. Since such an order is not a final judgment, we are without jurisdiction to consider the merits of his claim. Accordingly, the appeal is hereby dismissed.
